Field Descriptions: The Response Plan sales tax responsibility. This field is not a
component of the Patient Pay Amount (5Ø5-F5) formula.
The Response amount to be collected from the patient that is included
in ‘Patient Pay Amount’ (5Ø5-F5) that is due to the patient’s provider
network selection.
The Response  amount to be collected from the patient that is included in ‘Patient Pay
Amount’ (5Ø5-F5) that is due to the patient’s selection of a Brand product.
The Response  amount to be collected from the patient that is included in ‘Patient Pay
Amount’ (5Ø5-F5) that is due to the patient’s selection of a Non-Preferred Formulary
product.
The Response amount to be collected from the patient that is included in ‘Patient Pay
Amount’ (5Ø5-F5) that is due to the patient’s selection of a Brand Non-Preferred
Formulary product.
The Response amount to be collected from the patient that is included in ‘Patient Pay
Amount’ (5Ø5-F5) that is due to the patient being in the coverage gap (for example

The Response  informational field used when Other Payer-Patient Responsibility
Amount (352-NQ) or Patient Pay Amount (5Ø5-F5) is used for reimbursement. Amount
is equal to contracted or reimbursable amount for product being dispensed.
The Response informational field used when Other Payer-Patient Responsibility
Amount (352-NQ) or Patient Pay Amount (5Ø5-F5) is used for reimbursement. Amount
is equal to contracted or reimbursable dispensing fee for product being dispensed.
The Plan Id associated with the transaction as transmitted back to the
provider.
Must only have one value per iteration - value must not be repeated

02=Initial Benefit
